Serbian Juice Maker Nectar Mulls Fructal Takeover, Danas Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-03-28T08:31:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/serbian-juice-maker-nectar-mulls-fructal-takeover-danas-says.html
Serbian beverage maker  Nectar d.o.o 
is among potential bidders for Slovenian rival Fructal,  Danas 
newspaper reported, citing Nectar General Manager Bojan Radun.  Fructal is being offered by  Pivovarna Lasko (PILR)  Group d.d.
which is seeking about 50 million euros ($70 million) for a 93.7
percent stake in the juice maker, according to the report. The
newspaper said Nectar may be competing against  Italy ’s  Aqua
Minerale San Benedetto SpA ,  Germany ’s Eckes-Granini Group GmbH,
Warsaw-based soft-drink maker Kofola-Hoop SA and local
authorities in  Slovenia  that are keen to keep Fructal a domestic
company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  